However Brandon, I still think you are underestimating how different in reality a tablet is from a smartphone.  A smartphone only ‘does everything’ a tablet does in terms of the way it runs software.  For certain applications the difference in form is everything and makes a tablet a useful musical instrument, drawing board or a good reading medium, for example.  If you are just thinking of a tablet as something that can do everything a phone can, but with bigger text, then you are overlooking some of the attraction. <br><BR><font size=1>06:31 10-25-2012</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a></B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/heroclix/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=<a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a>'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#C3E3FF' ><font class="bfont">>>Neal disputed this and felt like it would replace actual computers. <br />
