I guess the only thing the Surface can&#39;t do is the iTunes and Zune stuff.  <br><BR><font size=1>16:10 10-24-2012</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Lt. Cabbage </B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/heroclix/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=Lt. Cabbage '>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">It really depends what you want to use a computer for and how much storage you need the device itself to have.<br />
<br />
The way I see it, there should be quite a few people who don&#39;t really need a computer at home to do much work other than the odd letter, maybe because they&#39;re retired or (and I&#39;m one of these) they are provided a computer at work.  Maybe it&#39;s only real purpose over and above what a standard tablet can do is to store photos.  In this situation, a Surface could fit the bill.<br />
<br />
The other common use is playing media, but consoles can handle that.<br />
<br />
There are various specialist uses that a full computer is wanted for (in my case music / DJing software), but not everyone will have that requirement.<br />
<br />
Screen real estate comes from having a monitor - most things can plug into one of those. <br><BR><font size=1>15:59 10-24-2012</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#C3E3FF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont"><B>The Don </B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/heroclix/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=The Don '>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#C3E3FF' ><font class="bfont">i wouldnt get a tablet to replace a desktop... i have at least a 23" screen on my desktop and a laptop or tablet cannot compare when i need the real estate and other things like optical drive.<br />
